caption: One of my preferred places to eat. good location, neat, and great service. 5 stars!

Incredible food, with every mouthful you taste the essence of the  food. The fish in wine sauce basically melts in your mouth, no overpowering taste. Beef bourgeoisie with steamed veggies was simply tasty. The bread they serve is soo delicious that you can get full quickly, pace yourself cuz you can not Miss the desserts. I get 2 things: creame brulee & chocolate muse cuz I can never decide. The staff is excellent too.
great food and great service
My wife and I think this is the best French restaurant in the city!

Food is absolutely divine. Foie gras ( the hot option) was substantial size and delicious. Steak tartare was very well balanced with flavors. Onion soup is a must to try! Duck was really good. Usually french restaurants have smaller portions but this restaurant offers good size portion and we really enjoyed it!  We got roses at the end of Valentine’s Day dinner which was such a nice touch. Love it.
Nice and cozy place with wonderful staff and amazing food.
Fabulous food and service a true French Bistro in Chicago
Excellent food and amazing service. Great neighborhood spot
Had the day's special (pork tenderloin) and creme brulee, both were amazing. Very nice atmosphere and great service, will definitely come back!
A top spot for french food. It's so delicious. The service was sociable and attentive. Feels similar to a cafe in Chicago I loved.
One of my favorite locations for French food. I love it here. Staff treated us so kindly. The bill was good for what you get.
French food, so great. food was super flavorful. the staff was very kind and attentive. menu is like a place in san francisco i liked.
Limited menu at least for the moment during Covid-19 but the Onion Soup and Beef Bourguignon were delicious.
It takes them one hour to decide to cancel my order on Ubereats.

On the last night of indoor dining in Chicago (for a while, anyway), we decided to enjoy our *only* meal out since the first shutdown in March.  Chez Moi was a fantastic choice. We were seated in the back dining room, and had an amazing experience. The escargot presentation with the puff pastry was really interesting and delicious. The steak tartare and onion tarte made equally great impressions. They have a great wine list, and the dessert list made us want to order one of everything.  Service throughout was excellent. Attentive, yet still appropriately distanced. I didn't catch our server's name, but he was wonderful.  Thank you for a wonderful last night out, and I wish you all the luck possible in the coming months.

Maybe not on a holiday...My husband and I went on Valentine's Day. We've never eaten French cuisine before. It was super packed and a set menu was provided. I will go again. Service was good. Profiteroles were overdone. Instead of golden brown. They were a little bit more on the dark side. All in all an enjoyable experience.
Very good wine great place to try authentic french food
A top scene for French food. The service here is friendly. This place has a nice design.

Ate outside although there is indoor seating , covid style.  Outside seating is first come first served, so reservation is irrelevant.  Nice brunch menu, generous portions, reasonably priced.  French classics are nicely prepared and presented.  Only complaint was eggs Florentine were a bit too salty for my taste.  Pleasant wait staff.

Not easy as french to find a real French restaurant .. with a french cook .. Not easy to cook french food with local supply.. Chez moi .. “at home”  could make it good..i had a cassoulet.. ( i am from southwestern France...) for the connaisseurs .. with a Lalande Pomerol ( Belles Graves) .. i had a great lunch time .. thanks to the team  nice people , clean ... And i would like to say to people sending negative comments .. Come on .. ! try again .. I will go through the menu in the coming weeks ...
Have eaten there a couple of times and gotten take out a few times recently. Always a very satisfying experience. The food has always been high quality, very filling, and excellently prepared.
french food and the atmosphere at this place is super good. i love this place so much. there was fast, efficient, and courteous service.

The food and drinks are DELICIOUS, the wait staff is so nice, and the decor is very aesthetically pleasing. Outdoor seating isn't too bad if you bundle up. Well worth the price, but you should expect to spend a good amount of money.
Went for mussels and loved them. Creme Brule was also great
One of my preferred spots for tasty french food. Great hospitality. The service was very welcoming and observant.

My boyfriend decided to take me out to diner for my birthday to this restaurant. He had made a reservation and they did not have a table ready for us until maybe 40 minutes later. Our waitress was very nice and charming I think she was the only good thing about this restaurant. While we had dinner I keeped seeing a rat 🐀 run back and forth though out the night and  at some point it ran under my feet it was disgusting!! Since it look them so long to sit us down we were last to finish eating our diner. The bus boy (older guy) keeped giving us the stink eye and was throwing things around he seemed unhappy that we were still there and ai guess was trying to make us leave. I though that was really rude specially since it was not our fault that we got situated late and to top it all off they charged us twice for champagne on our bill. I don’t even plan on going back to this restaurant ever again.
Nice atmosphere great food

The place serves big dishes and for reasonable pricing. friendly owner. Highly recommended.
Pricey but Tasty.
DELICIOUS escargot! Decadent and sumptous just as it should be! Desserts are just amazing too! Escargot, dessert, and a good champagne equals an amazing meal worth every penny!

We have loved every dish we've had in this gorgeous place.. finally got to try the patio tonight and I enjoyed the cassoulet for the first time, New York strip with frites and peppercorn for him, and an onion tart (best appetizer yet!) to share. Lovely cocktail list and wines as well.
One of my top locations for delicious french food. You will not be disappointed in the menu and service. I will be back with my friends. It has a nice feel to it.

This is one of my favorite spots in the City and it’s a go to for out of town guests. If you want a cozy and homey neighborhood feel coupled with amazing french food then this should be your #1 choice. Anyone still going to Mon Ami Gabi should give Chez Moi a try instead. In the summer, I always get the onion tart and mushroom ravioli. So. Good. When it’s super cold in the winter, my mom and I come for French onion soup and red wine on a weeknight. It’s heaven.
Delicious escargot and lamb shank.

This restaurant is my first choice restaurant.  Of all restaurants I know I love it most. I always suggests to my friends to go to that place. This restaurant is no doubt one of the tastiest place in the area. Anytime I go there I am absolutely happy. They hold their high  standard service and the highest level of dishes  they offer. You can never go wrong with this restaurant. Warmly  recommended.

I meet with friends this lovely place quite a bit! This is the best place to pass a nice evening.  I go there regularly. The food is very tasty, the crew is polite and the cost is reasonable. I like meeting in this restaurant for a tasty lunch.

The food was great! Everyone I went with had a feeling it would be good as there were multiple tables with customers speaking French to each other. Very clean, the staff was nice. One of my preferred places to grab something to eat. convenient location, always clean, and great service. 5 stars!

"Since it was a French restaurant I ordered French Fries and French Toast! (Just joking.) The waitress "Apolliana" (?) was very helpful. I have dental issues. But she recommended the Beouf Beguonne (French Pot roast was very good and easy for me to consume. The Merlot was just right. It was not too dry ( as Merlot wine usually tends to be.) A delightful surprise was their house version of a carbonated non-alcoholic beverage called Q-Soda with cherry juice. "Tres Bon!"

We had a wonderful experience in this spot. We loved the extraordinary vibes and the food. The waiters are very friendly. I am happy we ultimately decided to visit this place.

I call this marvelous  restaurant from time to time because I love the special air that is outline this place. The staff is extraordianrillyremarkably friendly and well trained. First time we went, we were encouraged. It was cute and had a neighborhood, cozy feel and a great wine list. Loved my asparagus salad. Soup was pretty bad, however. We overlooked that and went back for dinner a couple months later...service was cold and slow. Food was fine but overpriced. I was served a bad wine and it was literally dumped out in front of me, no apologies, no explanations. The general attitude is just kind of unprofessional. But they do coddle their regulars, so maybe that's why it's usually crowded. We're francophiles and this really isn't French.

From the moment  you arrive in that place  they give you a nice feeling. Very warm crew, it is a friendly place to hang out with friends and colleagues or with your date. delightful  food, qualified  chef, reasonable  price and nice  service. Warmly recommended.

Ate here yesterday with my friend and her family   We had many delicious appetizers, it’s hard to choose a favorite, but I think the hazelnut soup, escargot, and French onion soup have secured a little place in my heart! Almost didn’t have enough room for the main plate, but thankfully the kind waitress Athena recommended this incredible frisée salad that was mouth watering! I was just about stuffed when my friend order this beautiful plate of chocolate mousse and that was when chez moi secured themselves a new customer for life. Highly recommend for any kind of going out, you are missing out on incredible ambience and fine dining!

The chef is a genius. The food is amazing and the service is knowledgeable and friendly. I’ve been very impressed every time I dine at Chez Moi. If they have the Beef Wellington when you visit I highly recommend it!!!  Chez Moi now offers a dessert sampler! (MUST TRY)
The service is outstanding. The food scrumptious. I definitely recommend Chez Moi. Definitely try the French onion soup!

Went here for a date night with my girlfriend. I'm not from Chicago so I was hesitant, but we knew we wanted something upscale and romantic feeling. This place was perfect for the date, and the food was phenomenal. Highly reccomend the Gateau Breton Salidou for dessert.
I absolutely love this place, when I’m in town from Europe I always stop in to enjoy excellent food and a relaxing atmosphere with top service, well done to Dominique and India.
Tried this spot before with my friend and I am addicted since then. I loved the great vibes and yummy food and beverages. Highly recommended.
Great staff. Quiet side room. Wonderful food. Not handicapped accessible.

Outstanding food. Good selection of reasonably priced French wines.
The entire meal from appetizers to desert was 2nd to none. The atmosphere was charming and our server was informative & attentive but did not intrusive. I'll be back.
Great quiet spot for brunch in LP
The staff was friendly and attentive to our needs, and extremely personable. The food was very delicious!

Chez Moi was absolutely delicious for the appetizer, main course, dessert and wine. Onion tart was the appetizer - a little like pizza, and I don't know if that was traditionally French. Our mains were lamb shank with couscous and a sea bass fillet. Both were perfectly done and full of taste. However the climax was gateau Breton, a short cake which must have been made with a load of butter with sea salt caramel trim I've never had anything that tasted like that, and I hope to again. Even the wine and bread were good. Service was attentive, and the price, although steep, was worth it.

We had several small plates (the chilled pea with mint soup, the beet salad, the beautiful steamed artichoke, and then shared the mussels. The dishes were delicate, nuance and delicious. We agreed that it was the best French meal at a reasonable price that we have had in a long time.
Great service! Food is outstanding. The atmosphere is cozy and I will come back again for dinner.
Consistently tasty, healthy, beautiful food. Attentive service. 100% recommended!
Nice place. Attentive staff and great food. Well priced.

my expectations where much higher than the food i felt it can be special but lacked the complex flavors I have had with other French food.. Its a great atmosphere and great service just could have been more "impressed" by the food.. Sorry
Attentive service. I had the tres prix of trout, salad and creme brulee for dessert.  Froie gras appetizer and escargot. Everything was delicious!  Great ambiance. Street parking only
Had a really great meal and martini here. Boy was it expensive.

Very nice French brasserie style place in the heart of Lincoln Park, close to Theaters, like Steppenwolf. Have special and prix fixe menus too. Classic French staples, and some interesting New Orleans style dishes. Pretty decent wine list too. The prices are reasonable, in my opinion, too.

Absolutely the best French food in Chicago!!!!!! The food and wine selection was incredible. We love going on 1/2 wine nights! Just a piece of advice- get the soup and get the chocolate lava cake!!!!!! So goooooodddddd!!!!!!!
The staff was very friendly & helpful without being intrusive. Enjoyed the quiet atmosphere. The onion tart and blueberry & vodka drink were fantastic. We’ll be back!

Came in on Monday night (half priced wine bottle night 🍷👌).  Dined on the amazing lobster saffron broth seafood stew.  My friends went with the prix fixe and it looked incredible.
Great food, great wine, great service, cozy atmosphere, historic building. What more could you ask for?

I just want to talk about their community presence in Lincoln Park. They built a small herb garden that is meant to share with the neighborhood. You just have to ask and they will cut you some herbs. That amazing.

excellent food and atmosphere

The Moscow mule, lamb shank main course and the creme brulee are simply awesome! The appetizers we're just so-so or may be our pallette didn't quite appreciate it as much. Nice ambience for a get together with family/friends (not loud) and cozy n welcoming seating space. I would recommend getting in there early 7pm ish so you can pace yourselves along the courses.

Cozy restaurant that indeed looks like a French bistro. Service was great, including special attention and patience with our two kids. Food was delicious and, as expected, portions were small. Highly recommend.
I bought $20+ chicken that was dry and chalky 😑  I tried my friend's scallops which were delightful. Great customer service, but why did my plate have to be so bad?
Not authentic but good place to dine casually.

I enjoyed coming in during their weekday brunch. Unfortunately, they couldn't cut it, and had to return to a schedule of just weekday evenings. This is probably due to the fact that a lot of their food is prepared well in advance, their staff and management is a revolving door, and most importantly, Mon Ami Gabi is so much better. But I digress.  Now, I always found the Boeuf Bourguignon reliable. Until my most recent visit. Normally moist and tender, this time it came to me cold and dry. The mashed potatoes also were a tad gummy and gluey.  I decided to inform the manager. I believe his name is Chode? But per usual, he was distracted by friends, as he was far too comfortable and casual for them to be patrons. However, he did offer to give me 20% off for the inconvenience and a "nice reach around" if I was interested in following him downstairs.  I am not sure what a reach around is, but I hope it is not their "hard-as-rock" Brittany Cake.  Nevertheless, I will probably give them another chance in the near future. We will see if Chode can improve.
the mussels and onion tarte are wonderful to start off with. Order the lamb dish after with the Malbec and you will guarantee a good meal. Would definitely recommend and planning on going back.

Cozy atmosphere with delicious food. Stopped in for a drink and appetizer - ended up having the onion tart and squash pasta special. Delightful food and staff. Look forward to going back to try the roasted garlic!
Wonderful French food for not being in Paris. Wait staff on top of things. French onion bloody Mary's are outstanding!!! Yes ive been to Paris and i know good food!
Good food and a friendly staff.  The place for excellent French cuisine.
Cute quaint place. Attentive staff and great food. Well priced. Great place to go with a small group (4 people) friends or quiet date night. This place is becoming a regular place.

French dining from the Chef who reigned at Bistro 110. Excellent service, welcoming atmosphere with two dining rooms and white linens. Classic dishes like Duck a L'orange, Cassoulet  and Pate Fois Gras are graced with wine pairings with suggestions from a knowledgeable staff. Bread is a rustic brown,  not classic French baguette,  but dinner was memorable enough for us to plan a return visit.  Reservations recommended.

Amazing food with a fantastic atmosphere. Very nice touch seeing the owner interacting with all the tables and even help with the service of some of the food. Really feels like a home there.
Great staff! We had an amazing dinning experience! They we're so great with our kids.

Went here hoping for good French food and wasn't disappointed. The vibe of the restaurant is very French and the food was great. We ordered the cheese plate, carb cake, french toast and croissants. Everything was delicious, even the fries that came with the crab cake were on point (golden crispy on the outside and soft on the inside). The flavors are subtle and mixed well and the drinks were fresh. Kudos to the chef.

Solid French cuisine from  1. A real Frenchie 2. A veteran of the Chicago restaurant scene  The food here is very good and I love 1/2 Wine Bottle Mondays. Wish the menu reflected a bit more seasonal, but this is OUR fault.
Food was delicious, service was ok

Overall, it was very good.  Shared a few apps: charcuterie and pates. His pate is excellent. Not sure why the think sliced prosciutto was rolled up tightly? Thought it was odd. Good steak tartare.  Had the Cassoulet and it was pretty good. Cassoulet is one of those dishes that is very subjective and I like the beans to be creamier and the stock to be a bit richer/ meatier. Something where the stock is more gelatin/ sticky. But it was tasty.  Deserts here are very good.
Meh. Very bland coq so vin. Great wine, though.
Service and food was excellent

First class French food. I had the steak tartare and the vegetarian cassoulet, the latter of which was shockingly good. I wouldn't recommend the Apple tart for dessert, however. It had a bitter flavor to it that I couldn't put my finger on. Overall excellent and I would definitely come back. Very reasonably priced as well.
One of the most delicious spots in Chicago. Small chic Cafe with great food.
Fresh and delicious take on French fare!

Went for lunch at 2pm on Saturday November 10th. We had the French onion soup and lentil soup Absolutely delicious but we ordered the Steak fritz to share and they brought us the breakfast Steak fritz and if our server would have stopped by to see if everything was ok we could have gotten it corrected but 15 minutes later she did and we let her know that we didn't order that she said can I get you the one you wanted. We declined the problem with her is she offered no apology for her mistake. The manager was great he took it off the check.

Really solid French dishes. We tried 2 new menu items (the Wahoo & beef Madeira) which were both tasty. Profiteroles for dessert were okay, but maybe that is my preference and I just don't like them in general. The creme brulee was better in my opinion.

Yet another "Check Please" recommendation that didn't pass muster.  Only four tables filled at brunch, but they got both our orders wrong.  Eggs Benedict come with the smallest eggs I have ever seen.  Maybe they were using quail eggs.   And if you expect two eggs, don't make the mistake of ordering the Crab Benedict because it comes with only one teeny egg & the crab cake on one half the muffin, the other muffin half is empty.  It costs more though.  Side salad was OK but unremarkable.  Oddly, it was served with French fries.  OK, pommes fritte.    Call them what you will, even Mcdonalds doesn't use that much salt.   Coffee was hot brown water.  The bread was delicious! Hopefully they do a better job with dinner.
Delicious food from apetizer to dessert♡  Waiters were so gracious.
Cozy environment and excellent service. A nice place for date night!
A home away from home. very comfortable and delicious food.
Got desserts only. The chocolate mousse was excellent and a large portion. Creme brulee was great. The rustic bread they serve before the meal was actually my favorite part. Good wine too.

Great little gem. Very relaxed brunch. Lovely decor and awesome prices on brunch favorites like mimosas and bloody Mary's. Had the Crepes grande mere au gratin which was like a cheesy version of a Sheppard's pie. The warm apple tart we topped it off with was a good choice as well  Solid service, our waiter Sam, who I was disposed towards for obvious reasons, was attentive and even fixed up our mistake when it got confused as to whether we ordered a carafe of mimosas or bloody Mary's.

Honestly I'm so disappointed because last night I wanted a special treat by ordering just from the dessert menu.  Both of the dessert items one specifically recommended by my waiter and the one I decided to choose were bland, flavorless and most definitely isn't traditional French cuisine or pastry because ten years ago I visited Paris and I actually sampled traditional French pastries and desserts and what I received last night was just bad.  The server was very polite and chose dessert for me and I went with his suggestion and selected a gateau... resting on a gigantic moat of sweet caramel sauce and on top of the cake was a scoop of simple vanilla ice cream.  I bit into the butter cake but it was dry, heavy and bland.  I wanted to like it and I do have a sweet tooth but it wasn't tasty or creative nor pretty to look at .  All desserts here are way overpriced and for $9.25 i had expected my dessert to be flavorful and creatively prepared so the waiter took it back and I chose profiteroles instead but as pretty as they were I couldn't enjoy the floured hard biscuit pastry surrounding the vanilla ice cream .  I picked through my ice cream enjoyed the chocolate sauce and left the flavorless puff pastry dough behind.  He made a cocoa for me and since it wasn't a beverage they normally serve I was charged a fee of $4 and since it wasn't high end drinking chocolate I felt overcharged and underwhelmed.   I love sitting outside though and the service here was perfect but the desserts were so disappointing.  I came here to get desserts not dinner so I can't review the other items offered but I'm not sure I want to experience another meal here based on the bland desserts I tried.

It was a little expensive, but the groupon made it quite affordable and the food, ambiance, and decor were fantastic! A very classy place to have dinner with friends, or a great romantic spot for a couple.
Great food, service and ambience!
Wonderful country french experience and Chad is a warm and welcoming addition to Chez Moi.

Nice ambiance and decor. Service and personnel was pleasant. The food however had no flavor. Very disappointed in the taste and creativity. Not recommended if you are looking for French food or any king of food for that matter.
Pretty good food,  terrible service. Kitchen was slow, tables are too close together. Overall poor experience.
Great service. Phenomenal food. Wonderful attitude. What more could anyone ask!

Host was nice and friendly too, he stopped by our table a couple times to see how everything was going and our glades were never empty.

Overall: A fantastic French dining experience without being over-the-top classy, a great option for date night or to impress.  The good: Came here for a private event with a free 4-course meal along with wine pairings. The menu was fantastic. The pear salad was a perfect combo of sweet and creamy/savory with bleu cheese. The scallops were my favorite, drizzled with honey and a buttery polenta - a perfect combo. The lamb shank was also top notch, super tender and falling off the bone. The service was very friendly as was the main chef, who gave an intro and outro speech.  The not-so-good: The private room we were in was pretty cramped. The gateau breton was a little lackluster compared to all of the other magnificent courses, but it was still great.  Atmosphere: 9/10 Service: 9/10 Food: 9/10

Always in search for a decent French place, so ended up here upon recommendation of a friend. I also had the $35 Groupon for $65 worth of food. Ordered the mussels and the escargots. Mussels in Chicago always disappoint me, since they're so small, but at least the broth it was cooked in was delicious--- my friend went to town dipping her bread and the fries in the broth. I wasn't a fan of the escargot--- not flavorful enough--- they needed to salt the sauce. At least the puff pastry on top was an interesting touch.  Ordered the skate, which was prepared pretty well, but I still am just not a fan of skate. The rainbow trout had to be my favorite--- can't go wrong when you have fish and quinoa. Ordered the chocolate mousse for dessert, which was divine.  Our server was fantastic and super friendly. Good restaurant overall, but Paris Club still has to be my favorite for French food! -

Went here last Saturday with another couple and had a great time.  BYOB is awesome, parking is easy on the street or is very close to the brown line or metra.   Inside is cute and the staff were overall, very nice.  We had the duck, steak frites, and creme brule.  1. The duck was amazing and so well portioned for the price.  2. Steak frites were solid, but I'd say just a hair on the side of too done for a medium rare steak and 3. the creme brule was amazing.  Only off part about the night was when our entrees came out one was wrong and while it took us a few minutes to flag someone down one of the runners said "oh this is the wrong entree isnt it!" and he quickly switched us out, so I'm assuming there was just a mix-up.  When the waiter came around to apologize he more or less blamed the runner.  Fine, no biggie.  Then we put in our dessert orders and the wrong dessert comes out again (for the couple we were with) and nothing was really said about it.  I just find that a little annoying, but hopefully those kinks are worked out soon.
